@2 = ~This mod is not compatible with your game: check your install folder.~
@3 = ~Meraera's Dagger +2~
@4 = ~Dagger of Returning +2: "Meraera's Dagger"
An elven scholar-mage of the Olin Gisiae ("secret keepers") enchanted this dagger. She bound it with the essense of a minor demon and charged it to return to its thrower. Arcane runes wind around the hilt, but whatever meaning they possess is a well-guarded secret, like so much of Olin Gisir lore.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1D6 + 2
Special: Returns to hand once thrown
Equipped Ability: +1 attack per round
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Dagger
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 4 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Cleric~

@5 = ~Gethlun's Hammer +2~
@6 = ~This is the legendary hammer of a Stormlord of Talos named Gethlun, who some say attained demigodhood. Crafted by a duergar blacksmith long ago, Gethlun's Hammer possesses great powers. It confers electrical resistance, returns to the thrower's hand after being thrown, can never be destroyed, and was enchanted by Talos himself with the ability to control lightning.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2
Damage: 2D4 + 2
Special:
 Returns to thrower
 Lightning Bolt 3 times per day
 Call Lightning 3 times per day
Equipped Ability: Electrical Resistance +20%
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 4
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 15 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Mage
 Thief
 Monk~

@7 = ~Essembra Hammer +2~
@8 = ~The Essembra Hammer is named for its place of invention in the Dalelands. This polearm consists of a hammerhead with a spike at its rear, mounted on a long pole reaching practically ten feet in length. A long spear-like top-spike allows the wielder to keep enemies at bay and switch tactics to a deadly thrust attack. It is one of the heavier pole weapons and is rather slow. The entire weapon is made of steel, including the pole, and is decorated with carvings and precious metal gilding. This particular Essembra hammer bears a potent enchantment that can strike an enemy down or cause him to flee in abject horror.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1D8 + 2
Special:
 5% chance to knock unconscious
 10% chance to cause Horror
Damage type: crushing/piercing
Weight: 8
Speed Factor: 7
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 2-handed
Requires: 9 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Mage
 Thief
 Monk~

@9 = ~Aegis-Fang +3~
@10 = ~Aegis-Fang +5~
@11 = ~War Hammer +5: "Aegis-Fang"
Bruenor Battlehammer specifically made this weapon for Wulfgar, and the strongest of its enchantments only functions while in the young warrior's hands, where it is a +5 hammer. Anyone else wields Aegis-Fang as a +3 weapon.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +5
Damage: 2D4 + 5
Special: Returns to thrower
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 18 strength
Only Usable By:
 Wulfgar~
@12 = ~War Hammer +3: "Aegis-Fang"
Bruenor Battlehammer specifically made this weapon for Wulfgar, and placed a strong enchantment on it to return to its wielder when thrown. Bruenor takes great pride in this weapon - it is his finest work.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +3
Damage: 2D4 + 3
Special: Returns to thrower
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 18 strength
Not Usable By:
