@15 = ~War Hammer +3: "Dwarven Thrower"
This hammer - not to be confused with the elven-made Dwarf Thrower - is only usable by dwarves. In the capable hands of a dwarven warrior or priest, the hammer may be thrown at an opponent. The magic in the hammer draws it back to the hand of its wielder. If it hits an opponent, it does double the damage that a thrown hammer would normally do. Against giants and ogres, the hammer does an additional +8 damage due to the special hatred dwarves hold for these races.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +3
Damage: 2D4 + 3, +8 vs. giants and ogres
Special: Returns to thrower
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 4
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 9 Strength
Only Usable By:
 Dwarves
 Cleric
 Fighter (single and multi-class)~
@16 = ~Throwing Hammer~
@17 = ~Originally a blacksmith's tool, this simple hammer is composed of a steel head mounted on a 6" wooden shaft. It is balanced to deliver a bone-crushing impact when thrown.  Since the throwing hammer is designed differently than a normal hammer, it is less effective as a melee weapon.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1D4 + 1 (1D3 + 1 melee)
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 4
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 9 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Mage
 Thief~
@18 = ~Originally a blacksmith's tool, this simple hammer is composed of a steel head mounted on a 6" wooden shaft. It is balanced to deliver a bone-crushing impact when thrown. It is also the work of a master smith and exhibits a craftsmanship that makes it quicker and more effective in combat.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +1
Damage: 1D4 + 1
Damage type: missile (crushing)
Weight: 4
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 9 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Mage
 Thief~
@19 = ~Throwing Hammer +1~
@20 = ~Originally a blacksmith's tool, this simple hammer is composed of a steel head mounted on a 6" wooden shaft. It is balanced to deliver a bone-crushing impact when thrown. It is also enchanted, making it quicker and more effective in combat. Since the throwing hammer is designed differently than a normal hammer, it is less effective as a melee weapon.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +1
Damage: 1D4 + 2 (1D3 + 2 melee)
Damage type: missile (crushing)
Weight: 2
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 9 Strength
Not Usable By:
